snippet: The Republican-led State House voted Monday to complete an override of a veto by Gov. Mike Beebe, a Democrat, of a law requiring voters to show photo identification.
abstract: Arkansas' Republican-led State House votes to override Gov Mike Beebe's veto of law requiring voters to show photo identification.
lead_paragraph: The Republican-led State House voted Monday to complete an override of a veto by Gov. Mike Beebe, a Democrat, of a law requiring voters to show photo identification.
